properties.NAME: 299 Queen Street West
properties.ATTRACTION: A monumental building that was once dedicated to engaging the youth through popular music and popular television series.

properties.NAME: Aga Khan Museum
properties.ATTRACTION: Dedicated to sharing the artistic, intellectual, and scientific contributions that Islamic civilizations and cultures have made to world heritage.

properties.NAME: Al Green Theatre (at the Miles Nadal Jewish Community Centre)
properties.ATTRACTION: The Al Green Theatre is used  for social and corporate event, theatre, film, concerts, dance; and lectures.

properties.NAME: Alexander Muir Memorial Gardens
properties.ATTRACTION: Named after the famous composer Alexander Muir. The gardens act as a path into the tranquil ravine system that includes walking trails. The gardens are open year round.

properties.NAME: Allan Gardens
properties.ATTRACTION: Allan Gardens is a park and indoor botanical garden built in 1910. The building houses six greenhouses featuring plants and flowers from across the globe. Open year round and free to the public.

properties.NAME: Alumnae Theatre
properties.ATTRACTION: The theatre company is housed inside an old firehall and is the oldest theatre society in Toronto. Each year the company offers three productions.

properties.NAME: Arcadia Earth
properties.ATTRACTION: Arcadia Earth is a multi-sensory journey that combines creative art installations and exciting technology that showcases the beauty of our planet.

properties.NAME: Art Gallery of Ontario
properties.ATTRACTION: The Art Gallery of Ontario (AGO) is one of the largest art galleries in North America, and holds more than 80,000 works in its collection. In 2008 the building was redesigned by famous architect and native Torontonian, Frank Gehry.

properties.NAME: Art Museum at the University of Toronto
properties.ATTRACTION: Originally opened in 1996 The Arts centre puts a special focus on study collections.

properties.NAME: Artscape Wychwood Barns
properties.ATTRACTION: A heritage building converted into a community centre that hosts many events, festivals, farmers market and a children's theatre.

properties.NAME: Ashbridges Bay Park
properties.ATTRACTION: Ashbridges Bay waterfront park features large beaches, fishing areas, a marina, and the Woodbine Beach boardwalk.

properties.NAME: Balmy Beach Park
properties.ATTRACTION: Created in 1903, the historic park features a lawn bowling club, a playground and outdoor fitness equipment.

properties.NAME: BAPS Shri Swaminarayan Mandir
properties.ATTRACTION: This unique-to-Canada architectural monument is made with 24,000 pieces of marble and stone. Discover the more than 10,000-year-old heritage of India.

properties.NAME: Beanfield Centre
properties.ATTRACTION: The Beanfield Centre (formerly Allstream Centre) is an environmentally friendly conference venue.

properties.NAME: Betty Oliphant Theatre (at Canada's National Ballet School)
properties.ATTRACTION: Designed by Jack Diamond, the Betty Oliphant Theatre is used by the Canada National Ballet School as a training and performance venue.

properties.NAME: Billy Bishop Toronto City Airport
properties.ATTRACTION: Located minutes from the downtown core, Billy Bishop Airport serves nearby Canadian and American cities.

properties.NAME: Bluffer's Park and Beach (Scarborough Bluffs)
properties.ATTRACTION: Providing a beautiful backdrop for locals and visitors alike, the Bluffs are one of Toronto's great natural wonders.

properties.NAME: BMO Field
properties.ATTRACTION: BMO Field is home to the Toronto FC (Major League Soccer), Canada's national soccer team, and the home of the Toronto Argonauts (Canadian Football League).

properties.NAME: Bubble Planet
properties.ATTRACTION: Bubble Planet is an immersive experience featuring VR technology, illusions, ball pits and more.

properties.NAME: Buddies in Bad Times Theatre
properties.ATTRACTION: Buddies in Bad Times theatre is the biggest, and the longest-running queer theatre in the world.

properties.NAME: Budweiser Stage
properties.ATTRACTION: Located within the Ontario Place grounds, the Budweiser Stage offers concert goers an excellent outdoors venue.

properties.NAME: CAA Ed Mirvish Theatre
properties.ATTRACTION: A part of the Toronto theatre scene since 1920, the Ed Mirvish Theatre is a picturesque theatre to view special presentations ranging from concerts, comedy, plays, and many more.

properties.NAME: CAA Theatre (formerly Panasonic Theatre)
properties.ATTRACTION: Owned by Mirvish Productions, the CAA Theatre is the home of many famous theatrical productions.

properties.NAME: Campbell House
properties.PLACE_NAME: Sir William Campbell House Museum - Building Grounds
properties.ATTRACTION: The Campbell house dates back to 1822 and was once home to Judge William Campbell.  It is the last example of Palladian architecture in  Toronto.

properties.NAME: Canada's Walk of Fame
properties.ATTRACTION: Canada's Walk of Fame celebrates Canadians who have excelled in their respective fields for at least 10 years. The stars are displayed throughout the Entertainment District along King Street West and Simcoe Street.

properties.NAME: Canadian Museum of Cultural Heritage of Indo-Canadian
properties.ATTRACTION: The Canadian Museum of Cultural Heritage of Indo-Canadians is a museum committed to the understanding of India's rich cultural heritage. See BAPS Shri Swaminarayan Mandir.

properties.NAME: Canadian Sculpture Centre
properties.ATTRACTION: The Canadian Scultpture Centre is headquarters to the Sculptors Society of Canada. The society showcases and exibits contemporary Canadian scultpures.

properties.NAME: Canadian Stage (Berkeley Street Theatre)
properties.ATTRACTION: Home to the Canadian Stage Company, the Berkeley Street Theatre presents an array of Canadian and international performances.

properties.NAME: Casa Loma
properties.ATTRACTION: Canadas foremost castle is complete with decorated suites, secret passages, an 800-foot tunnel, towers, stables, and beautiful 5-acre estate gardens.

properties.NAME: Cedar Ridge Creative Centre
properties.ATTRACTION: Situated in a restored mansion, the centre features the Cedar Ridge gallery and rich gardens. The gallery highlights work from artists throughout the Greater Toronto area.

properties.NAME: Centennial Park
properties.ATTRACTION: Centennial Park is situated in Etobicoke and was opened in 1967 to celebrate Canada's 100th birthday. The park features sports fields, a conservatory, a ski hill, an Olympic size swimming pool, picnic areas and a Frisbee golf course.

properties.NAME: Centennial Park Conservatory
properties.ATTRACTION: The Centennial Park conservatory is located within Centennial Park. At a size of 12,000 square feet it features an arid house, a show house and a tropical house. The conservatory is open year round and is free to the public.

properties.ADDRESS_INFO: Located on Toronto Island - take ferry from 9 Queen's Quay West
properties.NAME: Centre Island Beach
properties.ATTRACTION: Centre Island Beach also known as Manitou Beach has been used by locals and tourists alike for more than a century. The beach is located on the south end of Centre Island. It is surrounded by park space and amenities such as bike and boat rentals.

properties.ADDRESS_INFO: Located on Toronto Island - take ferry from 9 Queen's Quay West
properties.NAME: Centreville Amusement Park
properties.ATTRACTION: Centreville is a 14-acre, turn-of-the-century, Ontario village theme park for children located on Centre Island, featuring over 30 rides.

properties.NAME: CF Fairview Mall
properties.ATTRACTION: An upscale shopping centre in the north eastern part of Toronto.

properties.NAME: CF Sherway Gardens
properties.ATTRACTION: An upscale shopping centre in Toronto's West end.

properties.NAME: CF Toronto Eaton Centre
properties.ATTRACTION: The Toronto Eaton Centre is downtown Toronto's only shopping mall. It features over 200 stores and restaurants as well as the sculpture called Flightstop designed by Michael Snow.

properties.NAME: Cherry Beach/ Clarke Beach Park
properties.ATTRACTION: Cherry Beach is located within the port lands and features a dog's off leash area, the Martin Goodman Trail and a picnic site.

properties.NAME: Chinese Cultural Centre of Greater Toronto
properties.ATTRACTION: The building houses the P.C. Ho theatre, studios, conference rooms, a resource centre, a reception hall and an art gallery.

properties.NAME: CN Tower
properties.ATTRACTION: The CN Tower is an engineering marvel and one of the city's most visited sites. It features the world's highest wine cellar, a fine dining revolving restaurant (360), a glass floor. For the true adventure seeker, the Edge walk.

properties.NAME: Coca-Cola Coliseum (formerly Ricoh Coliseum)
properties.ATTRACTION: Located at Exhibition Place, the Coca-Cola Coliseum is home to the Toronto Marlies (American Hockey League) and concerts.

properties.NAME: Colborne Lodge
properties.ATTRACTION: This quaint cottage located within High Park was home to John and Jemma Howard. In 1873 the couple deeded the part to lodge to the City of Toronto. The house is a great example of a regency style building.

properties.NAME: Dancemakers Centre for Creation
properties.ATTRACTION: One of Toronto's professional contemporary dance companies, Dancemakers and the Centre for Creation is focused on the delivery of refined and passionate dance to its admirers.

properties.NAME: Design Exchange
properties.ATTRACTION: Canada's only museum dedicated to the preservation of design which includes the design heritage from an array of mediums.

properties.NAME: Downsview Park
properties.ATTRACTION: The vast green space allows for an array of small-to-large scale events such as culture, dining, leisure, sports, and recreation.

properties.NAME: Elgin and Winter Garden Theatre Centre
properties.ATTRACTION: The Elgin and Winter Garden Theatre features two completely separate theatres and is the last running double-decker theatre in the world .

properties.NAME: Enercare Centre
properties.ATTRACTION: The largest convention centre in Canada, over 180 trade and consumer shows are hosted annually.

properties.NAME: Evergreen Brick Works
properties.ATTRACTION: A former brickyard, the Evergreen Brick Works is an urban model for ecosystem planning. Filled with activities for the whole family and a farmers market.

properties.NAME: Exhibition Place
properties.ATTRACTION: Attracting over 5 million visitors a year, this massive complex features sporting and exhibition facilities, a nightclub and attractions.

properties.NAME: Factory Theatre
properties.ATTRACTION: The Factory Theatre operates two theatres in a  Victorian mansion, where they have produced more than 150 Canadian plays, and various workshops.

properties.NAME: Famous People Players
properties.ATTRACTION: Located in Toronto's West End, Famous PEOPLE Players allows visitors to immerse themselves in a unique dining experience while enjoying theatre in the dark.

properties.NAME: Fort York National Historic Site
properties.ATTRACTION: Birthplace of Toronto in 1793 and scene of the Battle of York in 1813, Fort York has Canadas largest collection of original War of 1812 buildings. Open year round for tours, exhibits, and demonstrations.

properties.NAME: Four Seasons Centre for the Performing Arts
properties.ATTRACTION: The Four Seasons Centre for the Performing Arts is home to the Canadian Opera Company and the National Ballet of Canada.

properties.ADDRESS_INFO: Approximate address - Located on Toronto Island - take ferry from 9 Queen's Quay West
properties.NAME: Franklin Children's Garden
properties.ATTRACTION: The garden, inspired by Franklin the Turtle, is an area to discover nature, play, while learning something new.

properties.NAME: Gardiner Museum
properties.ATTRACTION: A museum dedicated to one of the oldest forms of art. The Gardiner Museum of Ceramic Art is home to over 3,000 historical and contemporary ceramic pieces.

properties.NAME: George Ignatieff Theatre
properties.ATTRACTION: In the Trinity College community, the George Ignatieff Theatre acts as a creative hub ranging from events like theatre, conferences, and much more.

properties.ADDRESS_INFO: Located on Toronto Island - take ferry from 9 Queen's Quay West to Centre Island
properties.NAME: Gibraltar Point Beach
properties.ATTRACTION: Surrounded by eastern cottonwood trees, the Gibraltar Point Beach is located on the southwest shore of Toronto Island Park. The Gibraltar Point Centre for the Arts is walking distance from the beach.

properties.NAME: Gibson House Museum
properties.ATTRACTION: Operated  by the City of Toronto, the Gibson House is a museum where visitors experience an exquisite farmhouse and learn more about the rural development of the area.

properties.NAME: Glenn Gould Studio
properties.ATTRACTION: Located on the main floor of the Canadian Broadcasting Centre,  the Glenn Gould Studio is a much-celebrated venue for its state of the art recording facilities and acoustics.

properties.NAME: Gooderham Flatiron Building
properties.ATTRACTION: Gooderham Building is a historic office building known for its unique location and triangular architecture.

properties.NAME: Graffiti Alley
properties.ATTRACTION: The graffiti hub showcases several blocks of colourful murals and art.

properties.NAME: Guild Park and Gardens (formely known as Guildwood Park)
properties.ATTRACTION: A sculptural alluring park and garden, the Guild Park and Gardens is rich in local history and a must-see for locals and visitors alike.

properties.ADDRESS_INFO: Approximate address - Located on Toronto Island - take ferry from 9 Queen's Quay West to Hanlan's Point
properties.NAME: Hanlan's Point Beach
properties.ATTRACTION: Situated on the west shore of Toronto Island Park, this beach is Toronto's only clothing optional beach.

properties.NAME: Harbour Square Park
properties.ATTRACTION: Located next to the Toronto Ferry Docks, Harbour Square Park offers downtown folks a spot to sit and watch the ferries travel back and forth to the island.

properties.NAME: Harbourfront Centre
properties.ATTRACTION: Popular 10-acre lakeside cultural site offers an eclectic blend of year-round arts, culture and recreation such as concerts, skating, music festivals and dance.

properties.NAME: Hart House Theatre
properties.ATTRACTION: A point of interest in the University of Toronto community, the Hart House Theatre and it's students produce an array of drama, dance, film, and music.

properties.NAME: High Park
properties.ATTRACTION: High Park is one of Torontos largest parks, and attracts visitors each spring for the blooming of its famous cherry blossoms. It also contains attractions and amenities such as recreational programs, a local zoo, a unique playground and a pond.

properties.NAME: Historic Zion Schoolhouse
properties.ATTRACTION: Built in 1869, the Historic Zion Schoolhouse has been restored to emulate schooling as it once was in the farming  district of L'Amaroux

properties.NAME: Hockey Hall of Fame
properties.ATTRACTION: Unique to Toronto, and featuring the Stanley Cup, interactive exhibits, shows, and the finest collection of hockey artifacts in the world.

properties.NAME: HTO Park
properties.ATTRACTION: Facing the inner harbour with Toronto Island Park in clear viewing,  HTO Park includes an urban beach which is decorated with yellow umbrellas and Muskoka chairs.

properties.NAME: Hudson's Bay
properties.ATTRACTION: Famously known as being North America's oldest company, the Hudson Bay is a chain of department stores  that operate throughout the country.

properties.NAME: Humber Arboretum
properties.ATTRACTION: Located nearby the West Humber River Valley, the Humber Arboretum offers trails through environmentally-rich areas like forests, and wetlands.

properties.NAME: Humber Bay Park West (Humber Bay Butterfly Habitat)
properties.ATTRACTION: Located at a waterfront park at the mouth of Mimico Creek, the Humber Bay Butterfly Habitat is focused on providing habitat for an array of native butterfly species.

properties.NAME: iArts Museum
properties.ATTRACTION: This unique museum features larger-than-life 3D illusions as an immersive experience.

properties.NAME: Illuminarium Toronto
properties.ATTRACTION: An immerseive experience featuring cutting edge visual, audio and projection technology, occasionally hosting shows.

properties.NAME: Isabel Bader Theatre
properties.ATTRACTION: Located at the University of Toronto, this multi-purpose venue seats 500 patrons whether it be for a lecture, workshop, or a theatrical production.

properties.NAME: Jack Layton Ferry Terminal
properties.ATTRACTION: Located at the foot of Bay Street and Queens Quay West, the  Jack Layton Ferry Terminal acts as a commuting point to and from the Toronto Island Park with frequent ferry service.

properties.NAME: James Garden Park
properties.ATTRACTION: Former estate gardens located in Toronto's west end that include rare trees, spring-fed pools, and other seasonal displays.

properties.NAME: Kew Gardens Park
properties.ATTRACTION: Located in The Beaches, Kew Gardens act as one of Toronto's most popular picnic grounds while having access to the boardwalk on the lakeshore.

properties.NAME: Koerner Hall (at the Telus Centre for Performance and Learning)
properties.ATTRACTION: Koerner Hall is a 1,135 seat venue to provide excellent acoustic sounds for all genres of music in its "shoebox" designed venue.

properties.NAME: Little Canada
properties.ATTRACTION: This attraction is an immersive joruney through the sights, sounds and wonder of Canada on a miniature scale.

properties.NAME: Mackenzie House
properties.ATTRACTION: Mackenzie House is the restored home of William Lyon Mackenzie, Toronto's first Mayor. It is one of 10 museums operated by the City of Toronto.

properties.NAME: Marie Curtis Park East Beach
properties.ATTRACTION: Located at the mouth of Etobicoke Creek near the foot of Forty-Second Street. Most users of this beach come from the bordering Long Branch community.

properties.NAME: Massey Hall
properties.ATTRACTION: Declared a heritage building in  the 1970s, this live events venue acts as a performance venue for various artists.

properties.NAME: Mattamy Athletic Centre
properties.ATTRACTION: Mattamy Athletic Centre is located within Maple Leafs Garden and is home to the Ryerson Ram's basketball, hockey and volleyball teams.

properties.NAME: Medieval Times Dinner and Tournament
properties.ATTRACTION: A family dinner theatre featuring staged medieval-style games, sword-fighting, and jousting performed by a cast of actors and horses.

properties.NAME: Mel Lastman Square
properties.ATTRACTION: A public park featuring 20,000 square feet of open space, a garden court, an outdoor amphitheatre, fountains and a reflecting pool.

properties.NAME: Meridian Arts Centre (formerly Toronto Centre for the Arts)
properties.ATTRACTION: This venue features three unique stages to house a multitude of concerts, shows and events.

properties.NAME: Meridian Hall (formerly Sony Centre for the Performing Arts)
properties.ATTRACTION: Meridian Hall is a performing arts venue with a range of events that include concerts, dance, and much more.

properties.NAME: Metro Toronto Convention Centre
properties.ATTRACTION: Offers more than 600,000 square feet of large exhibit, event, and meeting space.

properties.NAME: Montgomery's Inn
properties.ATTRACTION: A museum that was once a historic home, visitors can delve into the lifestyle of a 19th century Irish farm family with access to the bedrooms, kitchen wing and much more.

properties.NAME: Museum of Contemporary Canadian Art
properties.ATTRACTION: A variety of original and thought-provoking exhibitions, promoting innovative art by Canadian and international artists. Over 800 artists have been featured in more than 80 exhibitions and projects.

properties.NAME: Museum of Illusions Toronto
properties.ATTRACTION: The Museum of Illusions offers a wide array of mind-bending exhibits and optical illusions.

properties.NAME: Mysteriously Yours Mystery Dinner Theatre
properties.ATTRACTION: Mysteriously Yours. Mystery Dinner Theatre is a murder mystery dinner theatre located in  Downtown Toronto.

properties.NAME: Native Earth Performing Arts & Aki Studio
properties.ATTRACTION: Native Earth Performing Arts is a theatre company devoted to the artistic expression of the Indigenous experience. Located in Daniels Spectrum.

properties.NAME: Old City Hall
properties.ATTRACTION: Old City Hall is a landmark building that was used as Toronto's second City Hall and is a great example of beautiful architecture. Today, it is used as a courthouse.

properties.NAME: Onsite Gallery [at] OCADU
properties.ATTRACTION: Onsite [at] OCAD U provides the opportunity and space of an art gallery to exhibit students contemporary work.

properties.NAME: Osgoode Hall
properties.ATTRACTION: Constructed in the 19th century, Osgoode Hall acts as the judicial landmark of Toronto, with institutions like the Ontario Court of Appeal, the Law Society of Upper Canada, and the Divisional Court of the Superior Court of Justice.

properties.NAME: Polson Pier
properties.ATTRACTION: Located on the water, the Polson Pier is a waterfront property that includes a drive-in cinema, patio bar, concert venues, and much more.

properties.NAME: Princess of Wales Theatre
properties.ATTRACTION: Owned by Mirvish Productions. The Princess of Wales Theatre opened in 1993 and is the home  of many famous theatrical productions

properties.NAME: Queen Elizabeth Theatre
properties.ATTRACTION: Located at Exhibition Place, the Queen Elizabeth Theatre is an auditorium that is the venue for various entertainment events

properties.NAME: Queen's Park: Legislative Assembly of Ontario
properties.ATTRACTION: A variety of free tour options are available all year round to visit Ontarios historic Legislative Building (iconic sandstone Richardson Romanesque style building, completed in 1893).

properties.NAME: Randolph Centre for the Arts
properties.ATTRACTION: The historic Randolph Theatre is a 500-seat theatre located in a former Gothic revival style church.

properties.NAME: Redpath Sugar Museum
properties.ATTRACTION: Located inside the Redpath Refinery, the Redpath Sugar Museum is for those interested in the history of sugar, the development and the role of the Redpath family in Canada's industry sector, and much more.

properties.NAME: Ripley's Aquarium of Canada
properties.ATTRACTION: Canadas largest aquarium. Interactive attractions feature over 5.7 million litres of water and more than 16,000 marine animals.

properties.NAME: Riverdale Farm
properties.ATTRACTION: On 7.5 acres, Riverdale Farm is an historic working farm with many scenic pathways and farm animals.

properties.NAME: Riverdale Park (East and West)
properties.ATTRACTION: A Toronto park that is great for all seasons. Riverdale Park West has three multipurpose sport fields, seven tennis courts, an outdoor ice rink, two baseball diamonds, and much more.

properties.NAME: Rogers Centre
properties.ATTRACTION: The Rogers Centre is a multipurpose venue. Home to the Toronto Blue Jays (Major League Baseball) and the Toronto Argonauts (Canadian Football League).

properties.NAME: Rosetta McClain Gardens
properties.ATTRACTION: The Rosetta McClain Gardens is a great place to safely see the Scarborough Bluffs and has beautiful rose gardens. There are signs available in braille, textured paths, raised planters, and a ramp to ensure accessibility.

properties.NAME: Rouge Beach Park
properties.ATTRACTION: One of Toronto's designated swimming beaches, Rouge Beach has two distinct areas a white sand beach and a marsh habitat.

properties.NAME: Rouge National Urban Park
properties.ATTRACTION: Canada's first national park within an urban area, the park is Toronto's largest. It features hiking trails, a campground and Rouge Beach.

properties.NAME: Rouge Valley Conservation Centre
properties.ATTRACTION: The Centre focuses on environmental restoration and research while also offering interpretive walks and educational programs for the public.

properties.NAME: Roy Thomson Hall
properties.ATTRACTION: Opened in 1982, Roy Thomson Hall is home of the Toronto Symphony Orchestra and the Toronto Mendelssohn Choir.

properties.NAME: Royal Alexandra Theatre
properties.ATTRACTION: Owned by Mirvish Productions. The Royal Alexandra Theatre built in beaux-arts architectural style in 1907. It is home to numerous performances and performers.

properties.NAME: Royal Conservatory of Music
properties.ATTRACTION: The Toronto Conservatory of Music was founded in 1886.

properties.NAME: Royal Ontario Museum
properties.ATTRACTION: Canadas largest museum of natural history and world cultures, presents engaging galleries of art, archaeology, and natural science from around the world.

properties.NAME: Sankofa Square (formerly known as Yonge-Dundas Square)
properties.ATTRACTION: Yonge-Dundas Square is one of the city's largest public squares. It is located directly across from the Toronto Eaton Centre. The square is home to free movie screenings, concerts, shows and exhibits.

properties.NAME: Sarah and Chaim Neuberger Holocaust Education Centre
properties.ATTRACTION: The Sarah and Chaim Neuberger Holocaust Education Centre provides all its visitors a complete understanding of the Holocaust.30, 000 students pass through its doors during educational trips.

properties.NAME: Scarborough Museum
properties.ATTRACTION: The Scarborough Museum and its gardens are located within Thomson Memorial Park.It is one of 10 museums operated by the City of Toronto.The Museum looks back on the story of Scarborough's roots and history.

properties.NAME: Scarborough Village Theatre
properties.PLACE_NAME: Scarborough Village Recreation Centre - Building Grounds
properties.ATTRACTION: Theatre Scarborough is an umbrella organization consisting of Scarborough Music Theatre, Scarborough Players, and Scarborough Theatre Guild. Performances take place at the Scarborough Village Community Centre.

properties.NAME: Scotiabank Arena
properties.ATTRACTION: The Scotiabank Arena is a multi-purpose indoor sporting arena and concert venue. It is the home of the Toronto Maple Leafs Hockey Club, the Toronto Raptors basketball team, and the Toronto Rock Lacrosse team.

properties.NAME: Soulpepper Theatre Company
properties.ATTRACTION: Soulpepper is a not-for-profit theatre company that offers plays and concerts with a focus on training and youth projects.

properties.NAME: Spadina Museum
properties.PLACE_NAME: Spadina Museum - Historic House And Gardens - Building Grounds
properties.ATTRACTION: Operated by the City of Toronto, the Spadina Museum is a historic manor house that allows visitors to learn about the history and architecture of  late 19th century to early 20th century Toronto.

properties.NAME: St. James Park
properties.ATTRACTION: A large green space, home to a Victorian garden, live performances, and is a popular spot for photos. The park is adjacent to historic St. James Cathedral.

properties.NAME: St. Lawrence Centre for the Arts
properties.ATTRACTION: Home to  two theatres, the Bluma Appel Theatre and the Jane Mallett Theatre, the St. Lawrence Centre for the Arts is the home to various artistic and public events.

properties.NAME: St. Lawrence Market and Market Gallery
properties.ATTRACTION: Voted best fresh food market in the world by National Geographic in 2012, Torontos historic and premier market also includes The Market Gallery, housed within part of Torontos original 19th century City Hall.

properties.NAME: Steam Whistle Brewery
properties.ATTRACTION: A microbrewery located in downtown Toronto, Steam Whistle Brewery produces a premium pale lager composed of only four ingredients.

properties.NAME: Sugar Beach Park
properties.ATTRACTION: Sugar Beach is one of Toronto's urban beach parks. Famous for its pink umbrellas and Muskoka chairs.

properties.NAME: Sunnyside Beach
properties.ATTRACTION: One of Toronto's designated swimming beaches, Sunnyside Beach provides rowers and paddlers calm waters with an offshore break wall.

properties.NAME: Taras H. Shevchenko Museum
properties.ATTRACTION: The Taras H. Shevchenko Museum is the home to  exhibitions dedicated to the contribution of Ukrainians in Canada and the life of famed writer Taras Shevchenko.

properties.NAME: Tarragon Theatre
properties.ATTRACTION: The Tarragon Theatre is a performing arts centre  notable for the development of playwrights. Over 170 works have premiered at the theatre.

properties.NAME: Textile Museum of Canada
properties.ATTRACTION: With more than 13,000 objects from more than 200 countries and regions, the Textile Museum of Canada celebrates cultural diversity through traditional fabrics, garments, carpets and related artifacts such as beadwork and basketry.

properties.ADDRESS_INFO: Located in St. Andrew's Presbyterian Church
properties.NAME: The 48th Highlanders Museum
properties.ATTRACTION: This museum is dedicated to one of Canada's famous military regiments. The museum holds historical artifacts dating from Victorian Toronto in 1891, when the 48th Highlanders was formed, to the present day.

properties.NAME: The Bata Shoe Museum
properties.ATTRACTION: Home to hundreds of shoes (from a collection numbering over 13,000). The museum celebrates the style and function of footwear in impressive galleries from ancient Egypt to modern fashion.

properties.NAME: The Danforth Music Hall
properties.ATTRACTION: The Music Hall boasts new theatre seats, state-of-art sound and lighting and a completely renovated backstage area.

properties.NAME: The Distillery Historic District
properties.ATTRACTION: A pedestrian-only historic area that represents the largest and best preserved collection of Victorian Industrial Architecture in North America. The refurbished warehouses are now home to restaurants, bars, galleries, studios, and a theatre.

properties.NAME: The Image Centre (formerly known as Ryerson Image Centre)
properties.ATTRACTION: The RIC is dedicated to the public exhibition, research, study and teaching of photography including, installation art and film and media.

properties.NAME: The Japan Foundation
properties.ATTRACTION: A cultural establishment aiming towards effective development of its international cultural exchange programs in Japanese arts and cultural exchange.

properties.NAME: The Power Plant Contemporary Art Gallery
properties.ATTRACTION: Dedicated to contemporary art, the Power Plant is a free public gallery located at the Harbourfront Centre.

properties.NAME: The Second City
properties.ATTRACTION: Second City produces premiere comedy performances and operates a training centre.

properties.NAME: The Theatre Centre
properties.ATTRACTION: The Theatre Centre supports artists who wish to develop works of an experimental or alternative nature. All their artists embrace the visual arts, music, dance and new media.

properties.NAME: The Village Players
properties.ATTRACTION: The Village Playhouse a non-profit theatre group that opened its doors in 1974 and has since produced plays such as Cat on a Hot Tin Roof, Amadeus and Dial 'M' For Murder.

properties.NAME: The Well
properties.ATTRACTION: The Well opened in 2023, offering diverse dining experiences, retail stores and unique architecture.

properties.NAME: Theatre Passe Muraille
properties.ATTRACTION: Theatre Passe Muraille was Canadas original alternative theatre company. 600 Canadian plays have been produced since the company was founded in 1968.

properties.NAME: Thompson Landry Gallery - Stone Building & Cooperage Space
properties.ATTRACTION: The Thompson Landry Gallery is spread out over 6,000 square feet and showcases artwork from internationally acclaimed contemporary Quebec artists. The gallery opened in 2009 and is situated within the Distillery District's Cooperage Building.

properties.NAME: TIFF Bell Lightbox
properties.ATTRACTION: The TIFF Bell Lightbox is the home of the Toronto International Film Festival and a year-round destination for unique screenings, themed festivals, and exhibitions. It also houses two restaurants.

properties.NAME: Todmorden Mills Heritage Site
properties.ATTRACTION: Todmorden Mills Heritage Site is situated within the Don Valley and is located beside a 9.2 hectare wildflower preserve. It features historic buildings such as the Brewery building and the Papermill theatre and gallery.

properties.NAME: Tommy Thompson Park
properties.ATTRACTION: This narrow peninsula park is a perfect place for hiking, jogging, cycling and birdwatching, with 10km of paved trails.

properties.NAME: Toronto Botanical Gardens and Edwards Gardens
properties.ATTRACTION: Located at the stunning Edwards Gardens, Toronto Botanical Garden features award-winning themed gardens and an indoor education/interpretation facility.

properties.NAME: Toronto City Hall and Nathan Phillips Square
properties.ATTRACTION: Toronto's City Hall is one of Toronto's best known and visited landmarks. Nathan Phillips Square located directly in front of City Hall, is the site of  the iconic Toronto sign, concerts, farmers' markets, and iconic events.

properties.NAME: Toronto Congress Centre
properties.ATTRACTION: The Toronto Congress Centre opened in 1995 and now features over 1 million square feet of space for galas, meetings, trade shows and conventions,

properties.ADDRESS_INFO: Approximate address - Located on Toronto Island - take ferry from Jack Layton Ferry Terminal to Centre Island
properties.NAME: Toronto Island Park
properties.ATTRACTION: The Toronto Island Park is North America's largest car free neighbourhood and is only a short ferry ride away from downtown Toronto. The park is features several attractions, beaches, restaurants, bike and boat rentals and plenty of open green space.

properties.NAME: Toronto Metropolitan University Theatre (formerly known as Ryerson Theatre)
properties.ATTRACTION: Ryerson Theatre is home to various productions which includes concerts, film presentations, and Ryerson Theatre and Fashion Schools productions.

properties.NAME: Toronto Music Garden
properties.ATTRACTION: The Toronto Music Garden is situated on Toronto's newly revamped waterfront. The garden was designed by landscape designer Julie Moir Messervy and by the cellist Yo Yo Ma.

properties.NAME: Toronto Pearson International Airport
properties.ATTRACTION: Canadas busiest airport with flights to over 180 destinations around the globe.

properties.NAME: Toronto Police Museum & Discovery Centre
properties.ATTRACTION: The Toronto Police Museum & Discovery Centre occupies 3,000 square feet within the Police Headquarters building on College Street. The museum solely relies on private donations and is a not for profit registered charity.

properties.NAME: Toronto Railway Museum
properties.ATTRACTION: The Toronto Railway Museum encompasses the Canadian Pacific Railway John Street Roundhouse at Roundhouse Park and features a restored turntable, a number of trains and the 1896 Canadian Pacific Don Station.

properties.NAME: Toronto Reference Library
properties.ATTRACTION: The Toronto Reference Library is situated in a 5 storey building within the Yorkville neighbourhood. It is the largest public reference library in Canada.

properties.NAME: Toronto Sculpture Garden
properties.ATTRACTION: Since 1981 this small urban park has featured contemporary sculpture installations by various artists.

properties.NAME: Toronto Tourist Information Centre
properties.ATTRACTION: The Toronto Tourist Information Centre provides travel advice and information to all its customers. Services include free Wi-Fi service, brochures and souvenirs. Located at the entrance to the Skywalk.

properties.NAME: Toronto Zoo
properties.ATTRACTION: The Toronto Zoo is one of the largest zoos in the world at 287 hectares (710 acres) and is known for interactive education and conservation activities. It is currently home to 2 giant pandas, and more than 5,000 animals representing over 500 species.

properties.NAME: Toronto's First Post Office
properties.ATTRACTION: Toronto's First Post Office acts as a museum but also continues to operate as a full service Canada Post office. Admission to the museum is by donation.

properties.NAME: Travellers' Aid Society of Toronto
properties.ATTRACTION: Travellers' Aid Society of Toronto operates two desks; one at Pearson International Airport and the other within Union Station's grand hall. They offer free services to the general travelling public.

properties.NAME: Trinity Square
properties.ATTRACTION: Located in between the Toronto Eaton Centre and Old City Hall, the park features a fountain, ornamental pond, a labryrinth and seating; the park is a hotspot for music and events.

properties.NAME: Ukrainian Museum of Canada
properties.ATTRACTION: The Ukrainian Museum of Canada features over 4,000 artifacts. These artifacts include prints, coins, maps jewellery, textiles and historic costumes.

properties.NAME: Union Station
properties.ATTRACTION: Union Station is the busiest transportation hub in all of Canada. It serves more than 250,000 passengers daily. Via Rail, the TTC, Go Transit and Amtrak all operate out of the station

properties.NAME: Union Station Bus Terminal
properties.ATTRACTION: The bus terminal is the intercity transportation hub in Toronto.

properties.NAME: Village at Black Creek (Black Creek Pioneer Village)
properties.ATTRACTION: Become immersed in the lifestyles, customs, and surroundings of early residents who built the foundations for modern Toronto and Ontario at this 30-acre site.

properties.NAME: Village of Yorkville Park
properties.ATTRACTION: The Village of Yorkville Park was built on the site of a former parking lot, in the heart of the Bloor Yorkville neighbourhood. The main focal point of the park is the rock which weighs 650 tonnes and is approximately 1 billion years old.

properties.ADDRESS_INFO: Approximate address - Located on Toronto Island - take ferry from 9 Queen's Quay West to Ward's Island
properties.NAME: Ward's Island Beach
properties.ATTRACTION: Ward's Island beach is located on the most Eastern part of the Toronto Islands. It features a residential neighbourhood, 2 restaurants, a beach and boardwalk.

properties.NAME: Winchester Street Theatre
properties.ATTRACTION: The Winchester Street Theatre is owned and jointly operated by the Toronto Dance Theatre and the School of Toronto Dance Theatre. The venue features rake seating and a stage that best showcases dance performances.

properties.NAME: Woodbine Beach
properties.ATTRACTION: Woodbine Beach is one of the city's main beaches. The park is located over 15.2 hectares.  Features include the Martin Goodman Trail and the Donald D. Summerville Outdoor Olympic Pool.

properties.NAME: Woodbine Racetracks
properties.ATTRACTION: Offers both Standardbred and Thoroughbred racing and hosts many prominent events (including the Queens Plate)throughout the year.

properties.NAME: Woodbine Shopping Centre and Fantasy Fair
properties.ATTRACTION: The Woodbine Shopping Centre is located in the north western part of the city; close to Pearson Airport and Woodbine Racetrack. Fantasy Fair located within the mall is an indoor amusement park for children.  In 2015 it celebrates 30 years.

properties.NAME: Yorkdale Mall
properties.ATTRACTION: An upscale shopping centre in the northern part of Toronto.

properties.NAME: Young Centre for the Performing Arts
properties.ATTRACTION: Opened in 2006 the Young Centre for the Performing Arts has seen more than 250,000 people attend its performances. The theatre is located within the Distillery Historic District.

properties.NAME: Young People's Theatre
properties.ATTRACTION: The Young People Theatre is a part of the Soulpepper theatre company located within the Distillery Historic District.

properties.NAME: Yuk Yuk's
properties.ATTRACTION: Yuk Yuk's was established as a comedy club by Mark Breslin in 1976. It is located within Toronto's entertainment district and features various comedians doing their stand up routines.
